From 53109072d27f562d5b75edbd5deae16cad14b1dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tushar Darote <tdarote@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 14:17:40 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] litert: let find_package(flatbuffers) use the system
 package

litert/CMakeLists.txt looks for FlatBuffers with NO_DEFAULT_PATH,
restricting the search to the bundled TFLite build tree
(${TFLITE_BUILD_DIR}/...). When FlatBuffers is instead provided by the
toolchain/sysroot as a proper CMake package (flatbuffers-config.cmake
exporting flatbuffers::flatbuffers), NO_DEFAULT_PATH prevents it from
being found, so the code falls through to a hand-rolled IMPORTED target
pointing at ${TFLITE_BUILD_DIR}/_deps/flatbuffers-build/libflatbuffers.a
-- a path that does not exist in that configuration -- and the link
fails.

Drop NO_DEFAULT_PATH so the standard CMake search (CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH /
sysroot) is also consulted. When a system FlatBuffers package is present
its exported flatbuffers::flatbuffers target is used directly and the
fallback IMPORTED target is skipped; when it is not, the bundled build
tree PATHS are still searched exactly as before, so the existing
self-contained build is unaffected.

Upstream-Status: Submitted [https://github.com/google-ai-edge/LiteRT/pull/8465]
Signed-off-by: Tushar Darote <tdarote@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 litert/CMakeLists.txt | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/litert/CMakeLists.txt b/litert/CMakeLists.txt
index 0e329870..1f789c2c 100644
--- a/litert/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/litert/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -222,7 +222,6 @@ find_package(flatbuffers QUIET
       ${LITERT_FLATBUFFERS_BUILD_DIR}
       ${LITERT_FLATBUFFERS_DIR}/CMake
       ${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/flatbuffers-flatc/lib/cmake/flatbuffers
-    NO_DEFAULT_PATH
 )
 
 if(NOT TARGET flatbuffers::flatbuffers)
